<p>We are running our drive and turn feedback on our talonfxs for our swerve modules, and we are having some trouble with logging our robot’s drive kraken closed loop setpoints and errors. We have made sure to set the update frequency of the <code>StatusSignal</code>s and have made sure they are being refreshed every loop cycle, but the setpoint and error values are not changing.</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/b/0b20094bdd8eaef206a09dfdc1eeaac6bf6e5dfa.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/0b20094bdd8eaef206a09dfdc1eeaac6bf6e5dfa" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/0/b/0b20094bdd8eaef206a09dfdc1eeaac6bf6e5dfa_2_386x500.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="1ApT9R5xm2MqvXCyEkzj59XbEdY" width="386" height="500" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/0/b/0b20094bdd8eaef206a09dfdc1eeaac6bf6e5dfa_2_386x500.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/0/b/0b20094bdd8eaef206a09dfdc1eeaac6bf6e5dfa_2_579x750.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/0/b/0b20094bdd8eaef206a09dfdc1eeaac6bf6e5dfa_2_772x1000.png 2x" data-dominant-color="262525"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">837×1083 34.5 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>The robot drives perfectly fine, and in Tuner X, we can see the setpoint and error changing, which leads us to think it’s something to do with how we are calling getClosedLoopReference() and getClosedLoopError(). Is there anything obvious in this code that’s wrong or missing?</p>
